-- Italy’s February Government Debt Drops to EU1.93 Trillion
-- B y   C h i a r a   V a s a r r i
-- 2012-04-16T09:28:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/italy-s-february-government-debt-drops-to-eu1-93-trillion.html
Italian government debt narrowed to
1.93 trillion euros ($2.51 trillion) in February as the Treasury
used funds from its Central Bank account to meet borrowing
requirements, the  Bank of Italy  said today in its public-
finances supplement.  The euro region’s second biggest debt decreased by 6.8
billion euros from a month earlier, the central bank said in the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
